SA&#8217;s Cornelia Joubert has been named the winner of the ASA Half Marathon Championships Picture: Roger Sedres / Gallo Images Ethiopian athletes Genet Abdurkadi and Elisabeth Arsedo, who finished first and second in the women&#8217;s category at the ASA Half Marathon Championships at Pollok Beach on Saturday, have been disqualified for race number placement violations. SA&#8217;s Cornelia Joubert, who originally finished third, has been declared the winner with a time of one hour 12 minutes and 31 seconds. Gauteng North&#8217;s Stephen Mokoka won the men&#8217;s section in 1:01:21. Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share